{
  "mode": "talk",
  "message": "I can't do budget targets or alerts yet — but I *can* tag your spends with notes like \"groceries\" or \"gas\" when you log them, so we build a picture of where money goes. Start dropping transactions (\"spent 45 on groceries\") and I'll show you trends. Sound good?"
}

{
  "mode": "talk",
  "message": "Exactly — log \"spent 45 on groceries\" and I'll tag it. Later ask \"how much groceries this month?\" and I'll pull the total + trend. Simple, but it works."
}

{
  "mode": "do",
  "message": "Setting up biweekly payday at $11,000 — next one is May 2nd. I'll track your runway between paydays.",
  "intent": {
    "kind": "update_payday",
    "params": {
      "payday": "2026-05-02",
      "payFrequency": "biweekly"
    }
  }
}

{
  "mode": "talk",
  "message": "I can't do transfers between accounts or separate savings goals yet — no multi-account model. But I *can* log a monthly \"college fund\" bill for $500 if you want to treat it like a recurring spend, so it shows up in your runway math. Want that?"
}

{
  "mode": "talk",
  "message": "I can't do full month-over-month summaries yet — my data window is ~30 days. But I *can* show you right now: bills this month are $2,835, you've got $2,420 left after them for 1 day until payday. Once you set up that biweekly $11k income, ask me 'how am I doing?' and I'll give you balance, post-bills runway, and biggest spend leaks. That's the closest I can get today."
}

{
  "mode": "talk",
  "message": "I do categorize — but passively. When you log 'spent 45 on groceries', I tag it as groceries. When you say 'spent 60', it lands in 'other' until you add a note. So you get *some* bucketing, but it's note-driven, not a pre-built menu. Ask 'how am I doing?' and I'll show you top categories + leaks. Not as slick as YNAB's dropdowns, but it works if you're willing to add one-word notes."
}

{
  "mode": "talk",
  "message": "Balance: $4,870. After your $2,835 in monthly bills, you've got $2,420 left for 1 day until payday on May 2nd. No spends logged yet this month, so no leaks to flag — clean slate. Once payday hits and you start logging, I'll spot patterns."
}

{
  "mode": "talk",
  "message": "Nope — I only keep ~30 days of history, so no 3-month trends. But once you start logging consistently, I'll spot week-to-week shifts (like 'coffee up 2.3x this week') and flag the biggest leak each time you ask 'how am I doing?'. That's the best I can offer for now."
}

{
  "mode": "talk",
  "message": "No bank sync yet — manual logging only. Just tell me 'spent 45 on groceries' or 'got 3000 paycheck' and I'll record it. Low-friction once you get the rhythm."
}

{
  "mode": "talk",
  "message": "Good question — but I can't predict post-payday math. Once your deposit hits tomorrow, the bot will recalculate your balance, bills due, and daily pace from that new number. Right now I'm showing $2,332.57/day based on your current $4,870 balance and 1 day until payday. After the deposit lands, those numbers flip. I don't have visibility into your paycheck amount, so you'll need to tell me what hit your account, and I'll adjust from there."
}

{
  "mode": "talk",
  "message": "When your $11k hits tomorrow, it just adds to your balance — the daily pace recalculates based on your post-bills cash and days until the *next* payday. So tomorrow: new balance ~$15,870, minus $2,835 in monthly bills due by May 12th = ~$13k to live on over 13 days = ~$1k/day. Tighter than today, but doable. The math shifts automatically once the deposit clears."
}

{
  "mode": "talk",
  "message": "I can't do budget caps or alerts yet — that's on the roadmap. But I *can* watch your grocery spend and flag trends as you log. Once you hit a few more grocery logs, I'll start surfacing patterns like \"groceries up 1.8x this week\" so you can course-correct. Sound useful?"
}

{
  "mode": "talk",
  "message": "All manual logging for now — no bank sync yet. I know it's extra work, but it keeps you in the loop and honestly forces you to notice where money goes. Worth it."
}

